Text: Don’t believe the people who would rather have us addicted to chemicals than living a healthy life.
Since those in power do not care about us, we must take matters into our own hands.
Judges that are compromised by money and special interests must be removed.
We must act to end laws that favor any special groups or interests.
A government that would poison its citizens to control them must be removed.
Participation trophies coddle those who were too weak to win.
Our education system does not want to educate children - it wants our money.
Too much thinking leads to too little action.
Boys will be boys.
Fear regulates faster than reason.
Men lead, women nurture.
Taxes are just an excuse for corrupt officials to line their pockets with our money.
It’s not about our health - they are using us as guinea pigs for their own goals.
Tax the rich.
They’ve destroyed economic mobility to line the pockets of the rich.
The “neutral” are not neutral - they are hiding their complacency.
Rights are not negotiable, no matter how one behaves.
Our society doesn’t need reform - it needs a revolution.
We must have the courage to change the rules that hold us back.
We speak less when we are certain.
We must reward those who take the long road, not just the fast one.
Collaboration is better than competition.
It’s easier to criticize than to build.
Educating our kids should be this nation’s priority.
Children are our greatest wealth.
Kindness is not weakness; it’s a strength we to be proud of.
Our nation has always led the world not by force, but by example.
Our government weaponizes education to brainwash us.
The free market is a reflection of our basic human instincts.
Our most important responsibility is to support our family.
Our elders know best.
We should be proud of being softhearted; but we cannot afford to be soft-headed.
The greatest legacy is not wealth — it is wisdom.
We must be willing to share the benefits of our hard work with all.
Free libraries are necessary to ensure that every child is educated.
By lifting each other, we can make all of us stronger.
Humility is a virtue.
The our nationan spirit is about working together for a better tomorrow.
